75struct CSSPropertyBlendingContext : BlendingContext {
76 const CSSPropertyBlendingClient* client { nullptr };
77
78 CSSPropertyBlendingContext(double progress, bool isDiscrete, const CSSPropertyBlendingClient* client)
79 : BlendingContext(progress, isDiscrete)
80 , client(client)
81 {
82 }
83};

110static inline GapLength blendFunc(const GapLength& from, const GapLength& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
111{
112 if (from.isNormal() || to.isNormal())
113 return context.progress < 0.5 ? from : to;
114 return blend(from.length(), to.length(), context, ValueRange::NonNegative);

117static inline TabSize blendFunc(const TabSize& from, const TabSize& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
118{
119 auto blendedValue = blend(from.value(), to.value(), context);
120 return { blendedValue < 0 ? 0 : blendedValue, from.isSpaces() ? SpaceValueType : LengthValueType };
121}

123static inline LengthSize blendFunc(const LengthSize& from, const LengthSize& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
124{
125 return { blendFunc(from.width, to.width, context, ValueRange::NonNegative),

134static inline ShadowStyle blendFunc(ShadowStyle from, ShadowStyle to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
135{
136 if (from == to)
137 return to;
138
139 double fromVal = from == ShadowStyle::Normal ? 1 : 0;
140 double toVal = to == ShadowStyle::Normal ? 1 : 0;
141 double result = blendFunc(fromVal, toVal, context);
142 return result > 0 ? ShadowStyle::Normal : ShadowStyle::Inset;
143}

145static inline std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> blendFunc(const ShadowData* from, const ShadowData* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
146{
147 ASSERT(from && to);
148 ASSERT(from->style() == to->style());
149
150 return makeUnique<ShadowData>(blend(from->location(), to->location(), context),
151 std::max(0, blend(from->radius(), to->radius(), context)),
152 blend(from->spread(), to->spread(), context),
153 blendFunc(from->style(), to->style(), context),
154 from->isWebkitBoxShadow(),
155 blend(from->color(), to->color(), context));
156}

158static inline TransformOperations blendFunc(const TransformOperations& from, const TransformOperations& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
159{
160 if (context.client->transformFunctionListsMatch())
161 return to.blendByMatchingOperations(from, context);
162 return to.blendByUsingMatrixInterpolation(from, context, is<RenderBox>(context.client->renderer()) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*context.client->renderer()).borderBoxRect().size() : LayoutSize());
163}

165static RefPtr<ScaleTransformOperation> blendFunc(ScaleTransformOperation* from, ScaleTransformOperation* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
166{
167 if (!from && !to)
168 return nullptr;
169
170 RefPtr<ScaleTransformOperation> identity;
171 if (!from) {
172 identity = ScaleTransformOperation::create(1, 1, 1, to->type());
173 from = identity.get();
174 } else if (!to) {
175 identity = ScaleTransformOperation::create(1, 1, 1, from->type());
176 to = identity.get();
177 }
178
179 // Ensure the two transforms have the same type.
180 if (!from->isSameType(*to)) {
181 RefPtr<ScaleTransformOperation> normalizedFrom;
182 RefPtr<ScaleTransformOperation> normalizedTo;
183 if (from->is3DOperation() || to->is3DOperation()) {
184 normalizedFrom = ScaleTransformOperation::create(from->x(), from->y(), from->z(), TransformOperation::SCALE_3D);
185 normalizedTo = ScaleTransformOperation::create(to->x(), to->y(), to->z(), TransformOperation::SCALE_3D);
186 } else {
187 normalizedFrom = ScaleTransformOperation::create(from->x(), from->y(), TransformOperation::SCALE);
188 normalizedTo = ScaleTransformOperation::create(to->x(), to->y(), TransformOperation::SCALE);
189 }
190 return blendFunc(normalizedFrom.get(), normalizedTo.get(), context);
191 }
192
193 auto blendedOperation = to->blend(from, context);
194 if (is<ScaleTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get())) {
195 auto& scale = downcast<ScaleTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get());
196 return ScaleTransformOperation::create(scale.x(), scale.y(), scale.z(), scale.type());
197 }
198 return nullptr;
199}

201static RefPtr<RotateTransformOperation> blendFunc(RotateTransformOperation* from, RotateTransformOperation* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
202{
203 if (!from && !to)
204 return nullptr;
205
206 RefPtr<RotateTransformOperation> identity;
207 if (!from) {
208 identity = RotateTransformOperation::create(0, to->type());
209 from = identity.get();
210 } else if (!to) {
211 identity = RotateTransformOperation::create(0, from->type());
212 to = identity.get();
213 }
214
215 // Ensure the two transforms have the same type.
216 if (!from->isSameType(*to)) {
217 RefPtr<RotateTransformOperation> normalizedFrom;
218 RefPtr<RotateTransformOperation> normalizedTo;
219 if (from->is3DOperation() || to->is3DOperation()) {
220 normalizedFrom = RotateTransformOperation::create(from->x(), from->y(), from->z(), from->angle(), TransformOperation::ROTATE_3D);
221 normalizedTo = RotateTransformOperation::create(to->x(), to->y(), to->z(), to->angle(), TransformOperation::ROTATE_3D);
222 } else {
223 normalizedFrom = RotateTransformOperation::create(from->angle(), TransformOperation::ROTATE);
224 normalizedTo = RotateTransformOperation::create(to->angle(), TransformOperation::ROTATE);
225 }
226 return blendFunc(normalizedFrom.get(), normalizedTo.get(), context);
227 }
228
229 auto blendedOperation = to->blend(from, context);
230 if (is<RotateTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get())) {
231 auto& rotate = downcast<RotateTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get());
232 return RotateTransformOperation::create(rotate.x(), rotate.y(), rotate.z(), rotate.angle(), rotate.type());
233 }
234 return nullptr;
235}

237static RefPtr<TranslateTransformOperation> blendFunc(TranslateTransformOperation* from, TranslateTransformOperation* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
238{
239 if (!from && !to)
240 return nullptr;
241
242 RefPtr<TranslateTransformOperation> identity;
243 if (!from) {
244 identity = TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), to->type());
245 from = identity.get();
246 } else if (!to) {
247 identity = TranslateTransformOperation::create(Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), Length(0, LengthType::Fixed), from->type());
248 to = identity.get();
249 }
250
251 // Ensure the two transforms have the same type.
252 if (!from->isSameType(*to)) {
253 RefPtr<TranslateTransformOperation> normalizedFrom;
254 RefPtr<TranslateTransformOperation> normalizedTo;
255 if (from->is3DOperation() || to->is3DOperation()) {
256 normalizedFrom = TranslateTransformOperation::create(from->x(), from->y(), from->z(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_3D);
257 normalizedTo = TranslateTransformOperation::create(to->x(), to->y(), to->z(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_3D);
258 } else {
259 normalizedFrom = TranslateTransformOperation::create(from->x(), from->y(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE);
260 normalizedTo = TranslateTransformOperation::create(to->x(), to->y(), TransformOperation::TRANSLATE);
261 }
262 return blendFunc(normalizedFrom.get(), normalizedTo.get(), context);
263 }
264
265 Ref<TransformOperation> blendedOperation = to->blend(from, context);
266 if (is<TranslateTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get())) {
267 TranslateTransformOperation& translate = downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(blendedOperation.get());
268 return TranslateTransformOperation::create(translate.x(), translate.y(), translate.z(), translate.type());
269 }
270 return nullptr;
271}

273static inline RefPtr<ClipPathOperation> blendFunc(ClipPathOperation* from, ClipPathOperation* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
274{
275 if (!from || !to)
276 return to;
277
278 // Other clip-path operations than BasicShapes can not be animated.
279 if (from->type() != ClipPathOperation::Shape || to->type() != ClipPathOperation::Shape)
280 return to;
281
282 const BasicShape& fromShape = downcast<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*from).basicShape();
283 const BasicShape& toShape = downcast<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*to).basicShape();
284
285 if (!fromShape.canBlend(toShape))
286 return to;
287
288 return ShapeClipPathOperation::create(toShape.blend(fromShape, context));
289}

291static inline RefPtr<ShapeValue> blendFunc(ShapeValue* from, ShapeValue* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
292{
293 if (!context.progress)
294 return from;
295
296 if (context.progress == 1.0)
297 return to;
298
299 ASSERT(from && to);
300 const BasicShape& fromShape = *from->shape();
301 const BasicShape& toShape = *to->shape();
302 return ShapeValue::create(toShape.blend(fromShape, context), to->cssBox());
303}

311static inline FilterOperations blendFilterOperations(const FilterOperations& from, const FilterOperations& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
312{
313 FilterOperations result;
314 size_t fromSize = from.operations().size();
315 size_t toSize = to.operations().size();
316 size_t size = std::max(fromSize, toSize);
317 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; i++) {
318 RefPtr<FilterOperation> fromOp = (i < fromSize) ? from.operations()[i].get() : 0;
319 RefPtr<FilterOperation> toOp = (i < toSize) ? to.operations()[i].get() : 0;
320 RefPtr<FilterOperation> blendedOp = toOp ? blendFunc(fromOp.get(), toOp.get(), context) : (fromOp ? blendFunc(0, fromOp.get(), context, true) : 0);
321 if (blendedOp)
322 result.operations().append(blendedOp);
323 else {
324 auto identityOp = PassthroughFilterOperation::create();
325 if (context.progress > 0.5)
326 result.operations().append(toOp ? toOp : WTFMove(identityOp));
327 else
328 result.operations().append(fromOp ? fromOp : WTFMove(identityOp));
329 }
330 }
331 return result;
332}
333
334static inline FilterOperations blendFunc(const FilterOperations& from, const FilterOperations& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context, CSSPropertyID propertyID = CSSPropertyFilter)
335{
336 FilterOperations result;
337
338 // If we have a filter function list, use that to do a per-function animation.
339
340 bool listsMatch = false;
341 switch (propertyID) {
342 case CSSPropertyFilter:
343 listsMatch = context.client->filterFunctionListsMatch();
344 break;
345#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
346 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter:
347 listsMatch = context.client->backdropFilterFunctionListsMatch();
348 break;
349#endif
350 case CSSPropertyAppleColorFilter:
351 listsMatch = context.client->colorFilterFunctionListsMatch();
352 break;
353 default:
354 break;
355 }
356
357 if (listsMatch)
358 result = blendFilterOperations(from, to, context);
359 else {
360 // If the filter function lists don't match, we could try to cross-fade, but don't yet have a way to represent that in CSS.
361 // For now we'll just fail to animate.
362 result = to;
363 }
364
365 return result;
366}

368static inline RefPtr<StyleImage> blendFilter(CachedImage* image, const FilterOperations& from, const FilterOperations& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
369{
370 ASSERT(image);
371 FilterOperations filterResult = blendFilterOperations(from, to, context);
372
373 auto imageValue = CSSImageValue::create(*image);
374 auto filterValue = ComputedStyleExtractor::valueForFilter(context.client->currentStyle(), filterResult, DoNotAdjustPixelValues);
375
376 auto result = CSSFilterImageValue::create(WTFMove(imageValue), WTFMove(filterValue));
377 result.get().setFilterOperations(filterResult);
378 return StyleGeneratedImage::create(WTFMove(result));
379}

381static inline Visibility blendFunc(Visibility from, Visibility to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
382{
383 if (from != Visibility::Visible && to != Visibility::Visible)
384 return context.progress < 0.5 ? from : to;
385
386 // Any non-zero result means we consider the object to be visible. Only at 0 do we consider the object to be
387 // invisible. The invisible value we use (Visibility::Hidden vs. Visibility::Collapse) depends on the specified from/to values.
388 double fromVal = from == Visibility::Visible ? 1. : 0.;
389 double toVal = to == Visibility::Visible ? 1. : 0.;
390 if (fromVal == toVal)
391 return to;
392 double result = blendFunc(fromVal, toVal, context);
393 return result > 0. ? Visibility::Visible : (to != Visibility::Visible ? to : from);
394}

424static inline Vector<SVGLengthValue> blendFunc(const Vector<SVGLengthValue>& from, const Vector<SVGLengthValue>& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
425{
426 size_t fromLength = from.size();
427 size_t toLength = to.size();
428 if (!fromLength || !toLength)
429 return context.progress < 0.5 ? from : to;
430 size_t resultLength = fromLength;
431 if (fromLength != toLength) {
432 if (!remainder(std::max(fromLength, toLength), std::min(fromLength, toLength)))
433 resultLength = std::max(fromLength, toLength);
434 else
435 resultLength = fromLength * toLength;
436 }
437 Vector<SVGLengthValue> result(resultLength);
438 for (size_t i = 0; i < resultLength; ++i)
439 result[i] = SVGLengthValue::blend(from[i % fromLength], to[i % toLength], narrowPrecisionToFloat(context.progress));
440 return result;
441}

443static inline RefPtr<StyleImage> crossfadeBlend(StyleCachedImage* fromStyleImage, StyleCachedImage* toStyleImage, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
444{
445 // If progress is at one of the extremes, we want getComputedStyle to show the image,
446 // not a completed cross-fade, so we hand back one of the existing images.
447 if (!context.progress)
448 return fromStyleImage;
449 if (context.progress == 1)
450 return toStyleImage;
451 if (!fromStyleImage->cachedImage() || !toStyleImage->cachedImage())
452 return toStyleImage;
453
454 auto fromImageValue = CSSImageValue::create(*fromStyleImage->cachedImage());
455 auto toImageValue = CSSImageValue::create(*toStyleImage->cachedImage());
456 auto percentageValue = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(context.progress, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
457
458 auto crossfadeValue = CSSCrossfadeValue::create(WTFMove(fromImageValue), WTFMove(toImageValue), WTFMove(percentageValue));
459 return StyleGeneratedImage::create(WTFMove(crossfadeValue));
460}
461
462static inline RefPtr<StyleImage> blendFunc(StyleImage* from, StyleImage* to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
463{
464 if (!context.progress)
465 return from;
466
467 if (context.progress == 1.0)
468 return to;
469
470 ASSERT(from && to);
471
472 from = from->selectedImage();
473 to = to->selectedImage();
474
475 if (!from || !to)
476 return to;
477
478 // Animation between two generated images. Cross fade for all other cases.
479 if (is<StyleGeneratedImage>(*from) && is<StyleGeneratedImage>(*to)) {
480 CSSImageGeneratorValue& fromGenerated = downcast<StyleGeneratedImage>(*from).imageValue();
481 CSSImageGeneratorValue& toGenerated = downcast<StyleGeneratedImage>(*to).imageValue();
482
483 if (is<CSSFilterImageValue>(fromGenerated) && is<CSSFilterImageValue>(toGenerated)) {
484 // Animation of generated images just possible if input images are equal.
485 // Otherwise fall back to cross fade animation.
486 CSSFilterImageValue& fromFilter = downcast<CSSFilterImageValue>(fromGenerated);
487 CSSFilterImageValue& toFilter = downcast<CSSFilterImageValue>(toGenerated);
488 if (fromFilter.equalInputImages(toFilter) && fromFilter.cachedImage())
489 return blendFilter(fromFilter.cachedImage(), fromFilter.filterOperations(), toFilter.filterOperations(), context);
490 }
491
492 if (is<CSSCrossfadeValue>(fromGenerated) && is<CSSCrossfadeValue>(toGenerated)) {
493 CSSCrossfadeValue& fromCrossfade = downcast<CSSCrossfadeValue>(fromGenerated);
494 CSSCrossfadeValue& toCrossfade = downcast<CSSCrossfadeValue>(toGenerated);
495 if (fromCrossfade.equalInputImages(toCrossfade)) {
496 if (auto crossfadeBlend = toCrossfade.blend(fromCrossfade, context))
497 return StyleGeneratedImage::create(*crossfadeBlend);
498 }
499 }
500
501 // FIXME: Add support for animation between two *gradient() functions.
502 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=119956
503 } else if (is<StyleGeneratedImage>(*from) && is<StyleCachedImage>(*to)) {
504 CSSImageGeneratorValue& fromGenerated = downcast<StyleGeneratedImage>(*from).imageValue();
505 if (is<CSSFilterImageValue>(fromGenerated)) {
506 CSSFilterImageValue& fromFilter = downcast<CSSFilterImageValue>(fromGenerated);
507 if (fromFilter.cachedImage() && downcast<StyleCachedImage>(*to).cachedImage() == fromFilter.cachedImage())
508 return blendFilter(fromFilter.cachedImage(), fromFilter.filterOperations(), FilterOperations(), context);
509 }
510 // FIXME: Add interpolation between cross-fade and image source.
511 } else if (is<StyleCachedImage>(*from) && is<StyleGeneratedImage>(*to)) {
512 CSSImageGeneratorValue& toGenerated = downcast<StyleGeneratedImage>(*to).imageValue();
513 if (is<CSSFilterImageValue>(toGenerated)) {
514 CSSFilterImageValue& toFilter = downcast<CSSFilterImageValue>(toGenerated);
515 if (toFilter.cachedImage() && downcast<StyleCachedImage>(*from).cachedImage() == toFilter.cachedImage())
516 return blendFilter(toFilter.cachedImage(), FilterOperations(), toFilter.filterOperations(), context);
517 }
518 // FIXME: Add interpolation between image source and cross-fade.
519 }
520
521 // FIXME: Add support cross fade between cached and generated images.
522 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=78293
523 if (is<StyleCachedImage>(*from) && is<StyleCachedImage>(*to))
524 return crossfadeBlend(downcast<StyleCachedImage>(from), downcast<StyleCachedImage>(to), context);
525
526 return to;
527}

529static inline NinePieceImage blendFunc(const NinePieceImage& from, const NinePieceImage& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
530{
531 if (!from.hasImage() || !to.hasImage())
532 return to;
533
534 // FIXME (74112): Support transitioning between NinePieceImages that differ by more than image content.
535
536 if (from.imageSlices() != to.imageSlices() || from.borderSlices() != to.borderSlices() || from.outset() != to.outset() || from.fill() != to.fill() || from.horizontalRule() != to.horizontalRule() || from.verticalRule() != to.verticalRule())
537 return to;
538
539 if (auto* renderer = context.client->renderer()) {
540 if (from.image()->imageSize(renderer, 1.0) != to.image()->imageSize(renderer, 1.0))
541 return to;
542 }
543
544 return NinePieceImage(blendFunc(from.image(), to.image(), context),
545 from.imageSlices(), from.fill(), from.borderSlices(), from.outset(), from.horizontalRule(), from.verticalRule());
546}

548#if ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)

550static inline FontVariationSettings blendFunc(const FontVariationSettings& from, const FontVariationSettings& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context)
551{
552 if (!context.progress)
553 return from;
554
555 if (context.progress == 1.0)
556 return to;
557
558 ASSERT(from.size() == to.size());
559 FontVariationSettings result;
560 unsigned size = from.size();
561 for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
562 auto& fromItem = from.at(i);
563 auto& toItem = to.at(i);
564 ASSERT(fromItem.tag() == toItem.tag());
565 float interpolated = blendFunc(fromItem.value(), toItem.value(), context);
566 result.insert({ fromItem.tag(), interpolated });
567 }
568 return result;
569}

571#endif

583class AnimationPropertyWrapperBase {
584 WTF_MAKE_NONCOPYABLE(AnimationPropertyWrapperBase);
585 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
586public:
587 explicit AnimationPropertyWrapperBase(CSSPropertyID property)
588 : m_property(property)
589 {
590 }
591 virtual ~AnimationPropertyWrapperBase() = default;
592
593 virtual bool isShorthandWrapper() const { return false; }
594 virtual bool equals(const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&) const = 0;
595 virtual bool canInterpolate(const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&) const { return true; }
596 virtual void blend(RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext&) const = 0;
597
598#if !LOG_DISABLED

824static bool canInterpolateLengths(const Length& from, const Length& to, bool isLengthPercentage)
825{
826 if (from.type() == to.type())
827 return true;
828
829 // Some properties allow for <length-percentage> and <number> values. We must allow animating
830 // between a <length> and a <percentage>, but exclude animating between a <number> and either
831 // a <length> or <percentage>. We can use Length::isRelative() to determine whether we are
832 // dealing with a <number> as opposed to a <length> or <percentage>.
833 if (isLengthPercentage) {
834 return (from.isFixed() || from.isPercentOrCalculated() || from.isRelative())
835 && (to.isFixed() || to.isPercentOrCalculated() || to.isRelative())
836 && from.isRelative() == to.isRelative();
837 }
838
839 return false;
840}

873static bool canInterpolateLengthVariants(const LengthSize& from, const LengthSize& to)
874{
875 bool isLengthPercentage = true;
876 return canInterpolateLengths(from.width, to.width, isLengthPercentage)
877 && canInterpolateLengths(from.height, to.height, isLengthPercentage);
878}
879
880static bool canInterpolateLengthVariants(const GapLength& from, const GapLength& to)
881{
882 if (from.isNormal() || to.isNormal())
883 return false;
884 bool isLengthPercentage = true;
885 return canInterpolateLengths(from.length(), to.length(), isLengthPercentage);
886}

930class LengthBoxPropertyWrapper : public PropertyWrapperGetter<const LengthBox&> {
931 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
932public:
933 enum class Flags {
934 IsLengthPercentage = 1 << 0,
935 UsesFillKeyword = 1 << 1,
936 AllowsNegativeValues = 1 << 2,
937 };
938 LengthBoxPropertyWrapper(CSSPropertyID property, const LengthBox& (RenderStyle::*getter)() const, void (RenderStyle::*setter)(LengthBox&&), OptionSet<Flags> flags = { })
939 : PropertyWrapperGetter<const LengthBox&>(property, getter)
940 , m_setter(setter)
941 , m_flags(flags)
942 {
943 }
944
945 bool canInterpolate(const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to) const override
946 {
947 if (m_flags.contains(Flags::UsesFillKeyword) && from.borderImage().fill() != to.borderImage().fill())
948 return false;
949
950 auto& fromLengthBox = value(from);
951 auto& toLengthBox = value(to);
952 bool isLengthPercentage = m_flags.contains(Flags::IsLengthPercentage);
953 return canInterpolateLengths(fromLengthBox.top(), toLengthBox.top(), isLengthPercentage)
954 && canInterpolateLengths(fromLengthBox.right(), toLengthBox.right(), isLengthPercentage)
955 && canInterpolateLengths(fromLengthBox.bottom(), toLengthBox.bottom(), isLengthPercentage)
956 && canInterpolateLengths(fromLengthBox.left(), toLengthBox.left(), isLengthPercentage);
957 }
958
959 void blend(RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const override
960 {
961 if (m_flags.contains(Flags::UsesFillKeyword))
962 destination.setBorderImageSliceFill((!context.progress || !context.isDiscrete ? from : to).borderImage().fill());
963 if (context.isDiscrete) {
964 // It is important we have this non-interpolated shortcut because certain CSS properties
965 // represented as a LengthBox, such as border-image-slice, don't know how to deal with
966 // calculated Length values, see for instance valueForImageSliceSide(const Length&).
967 (destination.*m_setter)(context.progress ? LengthBox(value(to)) : LengthBox(value(from)));
968 return;
969 }
970 auto valueRange = m_flags.contains(Flags::AllowsNegativeValues) ? ValueRange::All : ValueRange::NonNegative;
971 (destination.*m_setter)(blendFunc(value(from), value(to), context, valueRange));
972 }
973
974 void (RenderStyle::*m_setter)(LengthBox&&);
975 OptionSet<Flags> m_flags;
976};

1191static inline const ShadowData* shadowForBlending(const ShadowData* srcShadow, const ShadowData* otherShadow)
1192{
1193 static NeverDestroyed<ShadowData> defaultShadowData(LayoutPoint(), 0, 0, ShadowStyle::Normal, false, Color::transparentBlack);
1194 static NeverDestroyed<ShadowData> defaultInsetShadowData(LayoutPoint(), 0, 0, ShadowStyle::Inset, false, Color::transparentBlack);
1195 static NeverDestroyed<ShadowData> defaultWebKitBoxShadowData(LayoutPoint(), 0, 0, ShadowStyle::Normal, true, Color::transparentBlack);
1196 static NeverDestroyed<ShadowData> defaultInsetWebKitBoxShadowData(LayoutPoint(), 0, 0, ShadowStyle::Inset, true, Color::transparentBlack);
1197
1198 if (srcShadow)
1199 return srcShadow;
1200
1201 if (otherShadow->style() == ShadowStyle::Inset)
1202 return otherShadow->isWebkitBoxShadow() ? &defaultInsetWebKitBoxShadowData.get() : &defaultInsetShadowData.get();
1203
1204 return otherShadow->isWebkitBoxShadow() ? &defaultWebKitBoxShadowData.get() : &defaultShadowData.get();
1205}
1206
1207class PropertyWrapperShadow final : public AnimationPropertyWrapperBase {
1208 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
1209public:
1210 PropertyWrapperShadow(CSSPropertyID property, const ShadowData* (RenderStyle::*getter)() const, void (RenderStyle::*setter)(std::unique_ptr<ShadowData>, bool))
1211 : AnimationPropertyWrapperBase(property)
1212 , m_getter(getter)
1213 , m_setter(setter)
1214 {
1215 }
1216
1217private:
1218 bool equals(const RenderStyle& a, const RenderStyle& b) const final
1219 {
1220 if (&a == &b)
1221 return true;
1222
1223 const ShadowData* shadowA = (a.*m_getter)();
1224 const ShadowData* shadowB = (b.*m_getter)();
1225
1226 while (true) {
1227 // end of both lists
1228 if (!shadowA && !shadowB)
1229 return true;
1230
1231 // end of just one of the lists
1232 if (!shadowA || !shadowB)
1233 return false;
1234
1235 if (*shadowA != *shadowB)
1236 return false;
1237
1238 shadowA = shadowA->next();
1239 shadowB = shadowB->next();
1240 }
1241
1242 return true;
1243 }
1244
1245 bool canInterpolate(const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to) const final
1246 {
1247 const ShadowData* fromShadow = (from.*m_getter)();
1248 const ShadowData* toShadow = (to.*m_getter)();
1249
1250 // The only scenario where we can't interpolate is if specified items don't have the same shadow style.
1251 while (fromShadow && toShadow) {
1252 if (fromShadow->style() != toShadow->style())
1253 return false;
1254 fromShadow = fromShadow->next();
1255 toShadow = toShadow->next();
1256 }
1257
1258 return true;
1259 }
1260
1261 void blend(RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const final
1262 {
1263 const ShadowData* fromShadow = (from.*m_getter)();
1264 const ShadowData* toShadow = (to.*m_getter)();
1265
1266 if (context.isDiscrete) {
1267 ASSERT(!context.progress || context.progress == 1.0);
1268 auto* shadow = context.progress ? toShadow : fromShadow;
1269 (destination.*m_setter)(shadow ? makeUnique<ShadowData>(*shadow) : nullptr, false);
1270 return;
1271 }
1272
1273 int fromLength = shadowListLength(fromShadow);
1274 int toLength = shadowListLength(toShadow);
1275
1276 if (fromLength == toLength || (fromLength <= 1 && toLength <= 1)) {
1277 (destination.*m_setter)(blendSimpleOrMatchedShadowLists(fromShadow, toShadow, context), false);
1278 return;
1279 }
1280
1281 (destination.*m_setter)(blendMismatchedShadowLists(fromShadow, toShadow, fromLength, toLength, context), false);
1282 }
1283
1284#if !LOG_DISABLED
1285 void logBlend(const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, double progress) const final
1286 {
1287 // FIXME: better logging.
1288 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << " blending ShadowData at " << TextStream::FormatNumberRespectingIntegers(progress));
1289 }
1290#endif
1291
1292 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> blendSimpleOrMatchedShadowLists(const ShadowData* shadowA, const ShadowData* shadowB, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const
1293 {
1294 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> newShadowData;
1295 ShadowData* lastShadow = 0;
1296
1297 while (shadowA || shadowB) {
1298 const ShadowData* srcShadow = shadowForBlending(shadowA, shadowB);
1299 const ShadowData* dstShadow = shadowForBlending(shadowB, shadowA);
1300
1301 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> blendedShadow = blendFunc(srcShadow, dstShadow, context);
1302 ShadowData* blendedShadowPtr = blendedShadow.get();
1303
1304 if (!lastShadow)
1305 newShadowData = WTFMove(blendedShadow);
1306 else
1307 lastShadow->setNext(WTFMove(blendedShadow));
1308
1309 lastShadow = blendedShadowPtr;
1310
1311 shadowA = shadowA ? shadowA->next() : 0;
1312 shadowB = shadowB ? shadowB->next() : 0;
1313 }
1314
1315 return newShadowData;
1316 }
1317
1318 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> blendMismatchedShadowLists(const ShadowData* shadowA, const ShadowData* shadowB, int fromLength, int toLength, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const
1319 {
1320 // The shadows in ShadowData are stored in reverse order, so when animating mismatched lists,
1321 // reverse them and match from the end.
1322 Vector<const ShadowData*, 4> fromShadows(fromLength);
1323 for (int i = fromLength - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1324 fromShadows[i] = shadowA;
1325 shadowA = shadowA->next();
1326 }
1327
1328 Vector<const ShadowData*, 4> toShadows(toLength);
1329 for (int i = toLength - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1330 toShadows[i] = shadowB;
1331 shadowB = shadowB->next();
1332 }
1333
1334 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> newShadowData;
1335
1336 int maxLength = std::max(fromLength, toLength);
1337 for (int i = 0; i < maxLength; ++i) {
1338 const ShadowData* fromShadow = i < fromLength ? fromShadows[i] : 0;
1339 const ShadowData* toShadow = i < toLength ? toShadows[i] : 0;
1340
1341 const ShadowData* srcShadow = shadowForBlending(fromShadow, toShadow);
1342 const ShadowData* dstShadow = shadowForBlending(toShadow, fromShadow);
1343
1344 std::unique_ptr<ShadowData> blendedShadow = blendFunc(srcShadow, dstShadow, context);
1345 // Insert at the start of the list to preserve the order.
1346 blendedShadow->setNext(WTFMove(newShadowData));
1347 newShadowData = WTFMove(blendedShadow);
1348 }
1349
1350 return newShadowData;
1351 }
1352
1353 const ShadowData* (RenderStyle::*m_getter)() const;
1354 void (RenderStyle::*m_setter)(std::unique_ptr<ShadowData>, bool);
1355};

1498 else

1500 }

1613 : FillLayerPropertyWrapperGetter<const Length&>(property, lengthGetter)

1648 if (fromEdge == m_farEdge)
1649 fromLength = convertTo100PercentMinusLength(fromLength);
1650 else if (toEdge == m_farEdge) {
1651 toLength = convertTo100PercentMinusLength(toLength);
1652 (destination->*m_originSetter)(fromEdge); // Now we have a calc(100% - l), it's relative to the left/top edge.
1653 }
1654 }

1732class FillLayersPropertyWrapper final : public AnimationPropertyWrapperBase {
1733 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
1734public:
1735 typedef const FillLayer& (RenderStyle::*LayersGetter)() const;
1736 typedef FillLayer& (RenderStyle::*LayersAccessor)();
1737
1738 FillLayersPropertyWrapper(CSSPropertyID property, LayersGetter getter, LayersAccessor accessor)
1739 : AnimationPropertyWrapperBase(property)
1740 , m_layersGetter(getter)
1741 , m_layersAccessor(accessor)
1742 {
1743 switch (property) {
1744 case CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionX:
1745 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionX:
1746 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper = makeUnique<FillLayerPositionPropertyWrapper>(property, &FillLayer::xPosition, &FillLayer::setXPosition, &FillLayer::backgroundXOrigin, &FillLayer::setBackgroundXOrigin, Edge::Right);
1747 break;
1748 case CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionY:
1749 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionY:
1750 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper = makeUnique<FillLayerPositionPropertyWrapper>(property, &FillLayer::yPosition, &FillLayer::setYPosition, &FillLayer::backgroundYOrigin, &FillLayer::setBackgroundYOrigin, Edge::Bottom);
1751 break;
1752 case CSSPropertyBackgroundSize:
1753 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundSize:
1754 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskSize:
1755 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper = makeUnique<FillLayerPropertyWrapper<LengthSize>>(property, &FillLayer::sizeLength, &FillLayer::setSizeLength);
1756 break;
1757 case CSSPropertyBackgroundImage:
1758 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper = makeUnique<FillLayerStyleImagePropertyWrapper>(property, &FillLayer::image, &FillLayer::setImage);
1759 break;
1760 default:
1761 break;
1762 }
1763 }
1764
1765private:
1766 bool equals(const RenderStyle& a, const RenderStyle& b) const final
1767 {
1768 if (&a == &b)
1769 return true;
1770
1771 auto* fromLayer = &(a.*m_layersGetter)();
1772 auto* toLayer = &(b.*m_layersGetter)();
1773
1774 while (fromLayer && toLayer) {
1775 if (!m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper->equals(fromLayer, toLayer))
1776 return false;
1777
1778 fromLayer = fromLayer->next();
1779 toLayer = toLayer->next();
1780 }
1781
1782 return true;
1783 }
1784
1785 bool canInterpolate(const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to) const final
1786 {
1787 auto* fromLayer = &(from.*m_layersGetter)();
1788 auto* toLayer = &(to.*m_layersGetter)();
1789
1790 while (fromLayer && toLayer) {
1791 if (fromLayer->sizeType() != toLayer->sizeType())
1792 return false;
1793
1794 if (!m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper->canInterpolate(fromLayer, toLayer))
1795 return false;
1796
1797 fromLayer = fromLayer->next();
1798 toLayer = toLayer->next();
1799 }
1800
1801 return true;
1802 }
1803
1804 void blend(RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const final
1805 {
1806 auto* fromLayer = &(from.*m_layersGetter)();
1807 auto* toLayer = &(to.*m_layersGetter)();
1808 auto* dstLayer = &(destination.*m_layersAccessor)();
1809
1810 while (fromLayer && toLayer && dstLayer) {
1811 dstLayer->setSizeType((context.progress ? toLayer : fromLayer)->sizeType());
1812 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper->blend(dstLayer, fromLayer, toLayer, context);
1813 fromLayer = fromLayer->next();
1814 toLayer = toLayer->next();
1815 dstLayer = dstLayer->next();
1816 }
1817 }
1818
1819#if !LOG_DISABLED
1820 void logBlend(const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const RenderStyle& destination, double progress) const final
1821 {
1822 auto* fromLayer = &(from.*m_layersGetter)();
1823 auto* toLayer = &(to.*m_layersGetter)();
1824 auto* dstLayer = &(destination.*m_layersGetter)();
1825
1826 while (fromLayer && toLayer && dstLayer) {
1827 m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper->logBlend(dstLayer, fromLayer, toLayer, progress);
1828 fromLayer = fromLayer->next();
1829 toLayer = toLayer->next();
1830 dstLayer = dstLayer->next();
1831 }
1832 }
1833#endif
1834
1835 std::unique_ptr<FillLayerAnimationPropertyWrapperBase> m_fillLayerPropertyWrapper;
1836 LayersGetter m_layersGetter;
1837 LayersAccessor m_layersAccessor;
1838};

1921class PropertyWrapperSVGPaint final : public AnimationPropertyWrapperBase {
1922 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
1923public:
1924 PropertyWrapperSVGPaint(CSSPropertyID property, SVGPaintType (RenderStyle::*paintTypeGetter)() const, Color (RenderStyle::*getter)() const, void (RenderStyle::*setter)(const Color&))
1925 : AnimationPropertyWrapperBase(property)
1926 , m_paintTypeGetter(paintTypeGetter)
1927 , m_getter(getter)
1928 , m_setter(setter)
1929 {
1930 }
1931
1932private:
1933 bool equals(const RenderStyle& a, const RenderStyle& b) const final
1934 {
1935 if (&a == &b)
1936 return true;
1937
1938 if ((a.*m_paintTypeGetter)() != (b.*m_paintTypeGetter)())
1939 return false;
1940
1941 // We only support animations between SVGPaints that are pure Color values.
1942 // For everything else we must return true for this method, otherwise
1943 // we will try to animate between values forever.
1944 if ((a.*m_paintTypeGetter)() == SVGPaintType::RGBColor) {
1945 Color fromColor = (a.*m_getter)();
1946 Color toColor = (b.*m_getter)();
1947
1948 if (!fromColor.isValid() && !toColor.isValid())
1949 return true;
1950
1951 if (!fromColor.isValid())
1952 fromColor = Color();
1953 if (!toColor.isValid())
1954 toColor = Color();
1955
1956 return fromColor == toColor;
1957 }
1958 return true;
1959 }
1960
1961 void blend(RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const final
1962 {
1963 if ((from.*m_paintTypeGetter)() != SVGPaintType::RGBColor
1964 || (to.*m_paintTypeGetter)() != SVGPaintType::RGBColor)
1965 return;
1966
1967 Color fromColor = (from.*m_getter)();
1968 Color toColor = (to.*m_getter)();
1969
1970 if (!fromColor.isValid() && !toColor.isValid())
1971 return;
1972
1973 if (!fromColor.isValid())
1974 fromColor = Color();
1975 if (!toColor.isValid())
1976 toColor = Color();
1977 (destination.*m_setter)(blendFunc(fromColor, toColor, context));
1978 }
1979
1980#if !LOG_DISABLED
1981 void logBlend(const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, const RenderStyle&, double progress) const final
1982 {
1983 // FIXME: better logging.
1984 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << " blending SVGPaint at " << TextStream::FormatNumberRespectingIntegers(progress));
1985 }
1986#endif
1987
1988 SVGPaintType (RenderStyle::*m_paintTypeGetter)() const;
1989 Color (RenderStyle::*m_getter)() const;
1990 void (RenderStyle::*m_setter)(const Color&);
1991};

2028template <typename T>
2029class AutoPropertyWrapper final : public PropertyWrapper<T> {
2030 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
2031public:
2032 AutoPropertyWrapper(CSSPropertyID property, T (RenderStyle::*getter)() const, void (RenderStyle::*setter)(T), bool (RenderStyle::*autoGetter)() const, void (RenderStyle::*autoSetter)(), std::optional<T> minValue = std::nullopt)
2033 : PropertyWrapper<T>(property, getter, setter)
2034 , m_autoGetter(autoGetter)
2035 , m_autoSetter(autoSetter)
2036 , m_minValue(minValue)
2037 {
2038 }
2039
2040private:
2041 bool canInterpolate(const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to) const final
2042 {
2043 return !(from.*m_autoGetter)() && !(to.*m_autoGetter)();
2044 }
2045
2046 void blend(RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, const CSSPropertyBlendingContext& context) const final
2047 {
2048 auto blendedValue = blendFunc(this->value(from), this->value(to), context);
2049 if (m_minValue)
2050 blendedValue = blendedValue > *m_minValue ? blendedValue : *m_minValue;
2051 (destination.*this->m_setter)(blendedValue);
2052
2053 if (!context.isDiscrete)
2054 return;
2055
2056 ASSERT(!context.progress || context.progress == 1.0);
2057 if (!context.progress) {
2058 if ((from.*m_autoGetter)())
2059 (destination.*m_autoSetter)();
2060 } else {
2061 if ((to.*m_autoGetter)())
2062 (destination.*m_autoSetter)();
2063 }
2064 }
2065
2066 bool (RenderStyle::*m_autoGetter)() const;
2067 void (RenderStyle::*m_autoSetter)();
2068 std::optional<T> m_minValue;
2069};

2540 const unsigned animatableLonghandPropertiesCount = WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(animatableLonghandPropertyWrappers);
2541
2542 static const CSSPropertyID animatableShorthandProperties[] = {
2543 CSSPropertyBackground, // for background-color, background-position, background-image
2544 CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition,
2545 CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeat,
2546 CSSPropertyFont, // for font-size, font-weight
2547 CSSPropertyWebkitMask, // for mask-position
2548 CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPosition,
2549 CSSPropertyBorderTop, CSSPropertyBorderRight, CSSPropertyBorderBottom, CSSPropertyBorderLeft,
2550 CSSPropertyBorderColor,
2551 CSSPropertyBorderRadius,
2552 CSSPropertyBorderWidth,
2553 CSSPropertyBorder,
2554 CSSPropertyBorderImage,
2555 CSSPropertyBorderSpacing,
2556 CSSPropertyListStyle, // for list-style-image
2557 CSSPropertyMargin,
2558 CSSPropertyOutline,
2559 CSSPropertyPadding,
2560 CSSPropertyPageBreakAfter,
2561 CSSPropertyPageBreakBefore,
2562 CSSPropertyPageBreakInside,
2563 CSSPropertyWebkitTextStroke,
2564 CSSPropertyColumnRule,
2565 CSSPropertyWebkitBorderRadius,
2566 CSSPropertyTransformOrigin,
2567 CSSPropertyPerspectiveOrigin
2568 };
2569 const unsigned animatableShorthandPropertiesCount = WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(animatableShorthandProperties);
2570
2571 // TODO:
2572 //
2573 // CSSPropertyVerticalAlign
2574 //
2575 // Compound properties that have components that should be animatable:
2576 //
2577 // CSSPropertyColumns
2578 // CSSPropertyWebkitBoxReflect
2579
2580 // Make sure unused slots have a value
2581 for (int i = 0; i < numCSSProperties; ++i)
2582 m_propertyToIdMap[i] = cInvalidPropertyWrapperIndex;
2583
2584 COMPILE_ASSERT(animatableLonghandPropertiesCount + animatableShorthandPropertiesCount < UCHAR_MAX, numberOfAnimatablePropertiesMustBeLessThanUCharMax);
2585 m_propertyWrappers.reserveInitialCapacity(animatableLonghandPropertiesCount + animatableShorthandPropertiesCount);
2586
2587 // First we put the non-shorthand property wrappers into the map, so the shorthand-building
2588 // code can find them.
2589
2590 for (unsigned i = 0; i < animatableLonghandPropertiesCount; ++i) {
2591 AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper = animatableLonghandPropertyWrappers[i];
2592 m_propertyWrappers.uncheckedAppend(std::unique_ptr<AnimationPropertyWrapperBase>(wrapper));
2593 indexFromPropertyID(wrapper->property()) = i;
2594 }
2595
2596 for (size_t i = 0; i < animatableShorthandPropertiesCount; ++i) {
2597 CSSPropertyID propertyID = animatableShorthandProperties[i];
2598 auto shorthand = shorthandForProperty(propertyID);
2599 if (!shorthand.length())
2600 continue;
2601
2602 Vector<AnimationPropertyWrapperBase*> longhandWrappers;
2603 longhandWrappers.reserveInitialCapacity(shorthand.length());
2604 for (auto longhand : shorthand) {
2605 unsigned wrapperIndex = indexFromPropertyID(longhand);
2606 if (wrapperIndex == cInvalidPropertyWrapperIndex)
2607 continue;
2608 ASSERT(m_propertyWrappers[wrapperIndex]);
2609 longhandWrappers.uncheckedAppend(m_propertyWrappers[wrapperIndex].get());
2610 }
2611
2612 m_propertyWrappers.uncheckedAppend(makeUnique<ShorthandPropertyWrapper>(propertyID, WTFMove(longhandWrappers)));
2613 indexFromPropertyID(propertyID) = animatableLonghandPropertiesCount + i;
2614 }
2615}
2616
2617static bool gatherEnclosingShorthandProperties(CSSPropertyID property, AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper, HashSet<CSSPropertyID>& propertySet)
2618{
2619 if (!wrapper->isShorthandWrapper())
2620 return false;
2621
2622 ShorthandPropertyWrapper* shorthandWrapper = static_cast<ShorthandPropertyWrapper*>(wrapper);
2623 bool contained = false;
2624 for (auto& currWrapper : shorthandWrapper->propertyWrappers()) {
2625 if (gatherEnclosingShorthandProperties(property, currWrapper, propertySet) || currWrapper->property() == property)
2626 contained = true;
2627 }
2628
2629 if (contained)
2630 propertySet.add(wrapper->property());
2631
2632 return contained;
2633}
2634
2635void CSSPropertyAnimation::blendProperties(const CSSPropertyBlendingClient* client, CSSPropertyID property, RenderStyle& destination, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to, double progress)
2636{
2637 ASSERT(property != CSSPropertyInvalid);
2638
2639 AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper = CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton().wrapperForProperty(property);
2640 if (wrapper) {
2641 // https://drafts.csswg.org/web-animations-1/#discrete
2642 // The property's values cannot be meaningfully combined, thus it is not additive and
2643 // interpolation swaps from Va to Vb at 50% (p=0.5).
2644 auto isDiscrete = !wrapper->canInterpolate(from, to);
2645 if (isDiscrete)
2646 progress = progress < 0.5 ? 0 : 1;
2647 wrapper->blend(destination, from, to, { progress, isDiscrete, client });
2648#if !LOG_DISABLED
2649 wrapper->logBlend(from, to, destination, progress);
2650#endif
2651 }
2652}
2653
2654bool CSSPropertyAnimation::isPropertyAnimatable(CSSPropertyID property)
2655{
2656 return CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton().wrapperForProperty(property);
2657}
2658
2659bool CSSPropertyAnimation::animationOfPropertyIsAccelerated(CSSPropertyID property)
2660{
2661 AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper = CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton().wrapperForProperty(property);
2662 return wrapper ? wrapper->animationIsAccelerated() : false;
2663}
2664
2665// Note: this is inefficient. It's only called from pauseTransitionAtTime().
2666HashSet<CSSPropertyID> CSSPropertyAnimation::animatableShorthandsAffectingProperty(CSSPropertyID property)
2667{
2668 CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap& map = CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton();
2669
2670 HashSet<CSSPropertyID> foundProperties;
2671 for (unsigned i = 0; i < map.size(); ++i)
2672 gatherEnclosingShorthandProperties(property, map.wrapperForIndex(i), foundProperties);
2673
2674 return foundProperties;
2675}
2676
2677bool CSSPropertyAnimation::propertiesEqual(CSSPropertyID property, const RenderStyle& a, const RenderStyle& b)
2678{
2679 AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper = CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton().wrapperForProperty(property);
2680 if (wrapper)
2681 return wrapper->equals(a, b);
2682 return true;
2683}
2684
2685bool CSSPropertyAnimation::canPropertyBeInterpolated(CSSPropertyID property, const RenderStyle& from, const RenderStyle& to)
2686{
2687 AnimationPropertyWrapperBase* wrapper = CSSPropertyAnimationWrapperMap::singleton().wrapperForProperty(property);
2688 if (wrapper)
2689 return wrapper->canInterpolate(from, to);
2690 return false;
